<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684839>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7.Cossura hutchingsae n. sp. Stereo microscope,C–G stained with methylen blue.(A) paratype,W.16338, dorsolateral view, gametes in the middle region are seen; (B) W.43346, anterior end, dorsal view; (C) paratype, W.42865, dorsolateral view (arrow indicates border between regions; chaetae bundles shifted to the middle of segments);(D) W.13652, anterior end, lateral view; arrowhead indicates mouth opening; (E) holotype, W.43372, anterior end, dorsal view; (F) holotype, W.43372, anterior end, lateral view; (G) W.43369, chaetigers 3–13, lateral view. Scale bars: A, D = 600 μm, B, E, F, G = 200 μm, C = 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4684839/files/figure.png" .

